After the fall of Alfheim, [[Amora (Earth-616)|Enchantress]] traveled to [[Earth|Midgard]] and enthralled the [[Amadeus Cho (Earth-616)|Hulk]] by offering him the position of King of the Ten Realms, then enraging him by forcing him to relive the deaths of [[Philip Cho (Earth-616)|Philip]] and [[Helen Cho (Earth-616)|Helen Cho]].{{r|Totally Awesome Hulk Vol 1 5}} While under her sway, Hulk robbed an outpost in [[Iceland]] where the [[Dwarves of Nidavellir]] were secretly storing [[Uru]] for fear of [[Nidavellir|their realm]] falling to the Dark Council's army. Thor arrived and confronted Amadeus over his assisting Amora; however, Hulk did not remember what had happened, though with the help of his sister, [[Madame Curie Cho (Earth-616)|Maddy]], he convinced the Goddess of Thunder to allow him to try to make amends. Ultimately tracking the stolen Uru to [[Eyjafjallajokull|Eyjafjallajökull]], the trio discovered that the [[Dark Elves]] had indeed been forging weapons in preparation of the invasion of [[Asgard (Realm)|Asgard]]. This time the Hulk resisted Amora's enchantment, allowing him to defeat the Dark Elves, and after being tased by Maddy, the Enchantress cursed the Cho clan as she fled. The Uru was returned to the Dwarves and Thor departed.{{r|Totally Awesome Hulk Vol 1 6}}
