After inflicting havoc over various realms, the Dark Council launched an all-out invasion of [[Earth|Midgard]] and quickly conquered much of the planet, dividing it up among themselves. The world's heroes were overwhelmed by the Dark Council's numbers and were forced to retreat to [[Avengers Mountain]]. There, they began planning a counterattack. Using the restored [[Bifrost]] manned by [[Matthew Murdock (Earth-616)|Daredevil]], a [[Jotunheim Strikeforce (Earth-616)|small team]] was sent into Jotunheim to rescue Thor who had been stranded there by Loki while [[Freyja Freyrdottir (Earth-616)|Queen Frigga]] led a team into [[Svartalfheim]] to destroy Malekith's [[Black Bifrost]], which what allowed the Dark Council to strike Midgard in so many places at once.{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 1|3}}

Thor was eventually rescued, and Frigga and her team were able to capture the Black Bifrost. When the Bifrost was destroyed by Dark Elf suicide bombers, the Black Bifrost was used instead to gather the various races that had been victimized by the Dark Council and organize a counterattack. Once everything was done, Frigga attempted to destroy the Black Bifrost but was stopped by Malekith. Before he could kill her, Odin came to her rescue while wearing a set of [[Iron All-Father Armor|armor]]. With their combined power, Odin and Frigga were able to destroy the Black Bifrost.{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 3|4}}

A massive counterattack was launched against the Dark Council and slowly Midgard was retaken. However, Malekith had used his dark magic combined with magic from [[Stonehenge (Location)|Stonehenge]] to turn the [[Venom (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Venom symbiote]] into his own magical blade. He also held Odin and Frigga hostage and demanded that Thor face him alone, or his parents would die. So, Thor nailed himself to [[Yggdrasil]] on the [[Sun (Star)|Sun]] to learn how to rescue his parents. After sacrificing his left eye and the last remnant of Mjolnir, Thor learned that he needed to gather other Thors to help him.{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 4|6}}

While Thor gathered past and [[Thor Odinson (Earth-14412)|future]] versions of himself, his allies began defeating the Dark Council's main players. Ulik, Amora,{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 6}} and Sindr were captured;{{r|Thor Vol 5 15}} the Minotaur was grievously wounded;{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 5}} and the Queen of Angels{{r|Asgardians of the Galaxy Vol 1 10}} and Laufey were killed. Thor, his past and future selves, and Jane Foster empowered by the Mjolnir from the [[Earth-1610|Ultimate Universe]] confronted Malekith at Stonehenge. Malekith at first was too powerful thanks to the powered Venom symbiote, but Thor was able to finally defeat Malekith by striking him with the reforged Mjolnir. The Venom symbiote separated from Malekith, and Malekith then lost one of his arms to the young Thor. Malekith attempted to rally his [[Hounds of the Hunter (Earth-616)|Wild Hunt]] and Bog Tiger, but they sensed his fear and devoured him.{{r|War of the Realms Vol 1 6}}

Ulik, Amora, and Sindr were later placed in a [[Yggdrasill|prison]] in Asgard made from the roots of Yggdrasil and watched over by the [[Warriors Three (Earth-616)|Ministers Three]]. The Minotaur ultimately survived his wounds and was able to escape blame for his role in Malekith's war by holding a press conference and stating that videos showing him participating in the war were doctored by [[Wakanda]].{{r|Thor Vol 5 16}}
